    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "CXR\nmay show visceral herniation\nPoorly sensitive\nCT chest/abdomen/pelvis with contrast may better detect smaller herniations (roughly 82% sensitive and 88% specific)\n[2]\n\"Collar sign\"\nwaist-like constriction of abdominal viscera\nMRI better evaluates the diaphragm itself in stable patients in whom the diagnosis is unclear\nSurgical exploration is ultimately the best diagnostic modality (thoracoscopy vs laparoscopy vs ex-lap depending on concurrent injuries)\nThoracoscopy\nLaparoscopy",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "CXR",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/CXR"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "NG tube\ndecompression\nSurgery is required to fix the defect",
      "subsections": {},
